ARE DIETARY SUPPLEMENTS ILLEGAL DRUGS? KEY COURT TEST IS NEAR.
Herbal medicine, the mainstay of therapeutics for centuriesbefore modern purified drugs relegated it to the status ofnear-quackery, has in the last five years emerged from the fringesof health care with an astonishing flourish and now shows clearsigns of joining the medical mainstream.
Alarmed by what they see as the potential for mishaps withpatients taking herbal remedies for everything from depression tomemory loss, anesthesiologists have begun urging people to stoptaking the herbs and supplements before having surgery.
They vow to help you trim down, boost energy, put muscle on, andeven take cellulite off.
